Thu Sep 25 16:01:49 UTC 2025 - Marcus Rueckert <mrueckert@suse.de>

- Update to 4.2.3 (CVE-2025-0218 boo#1235477)
  When batch jobs are executed by pgAgent, a script is created in a
  temporary directory and then executed. In versions of pgAgent
  prior to 4.2.3, an insufficiently seeded random number generator
  is used when generating the directory name, leading to the
  possibility for a local attacker to pre-create the directory and
  thus prevent pgAgent from executing jobs, disrupting scheduled
  tasks.

  The pgAdmin project thanks Wolfgang Frisch from SUSE for
  reporting this issue.

